fields.description: Any article page from Radiopaedia is eligible. Radiopaedia is the world's most comprehensive wiki on clinical imaging, with expert peer review.
Abstracts on PubMed are eligible. Pubmed is the world’s repository for peer-reviewed scientific abstracts.

fields.example_title: Guidelines for Management of Incidental Pulmonary Nodules Detected on CT Images: From the Fleischner Society 2017
fields.description: Either abstracts or articles from Radiology are eligible. Radiology publishes primary research articles and consensus guidelines that resonate with radiology.

fields.example_title: Imaging the Endometrium: Disease and Normal Variants
fields.description: Abstracts and articles from Radiographics are eligible. Radiographics publishes vivid and comprehensive reviews, accessible to radiologists at all levels.

fields.domain_title: AJR - American Journal of Roentgenology - ARRS
fields.description: Abstracts and journal articles are eligible. The American Journal of Roentgenology (ARRS) includes equal parts review articles and original research in radiology.

fields.example_title: Clinical applications of 7 T MRI in the brain
fields.description: Abstracts and journal articles are eligible. The European Journal of Radiology publishes broadly in radiology, including predominantly original research and some review articles.

fields.domain_title: JACR - Journal of the American College of Radiology
fields.example_title: Managing Incidental Findings on Abdominal CT
fields.description: Abstracts and journal articles are eligible. JACR publishes on the business and politics of radiology.
fields.page_title_suffix: - Journal of the American College of Radiology

fields.example_title: Generalized analog thresholding for spike acquisition at ultralow sampling rates
fields.description: Full-text articles on PubMed Central are eligible. PubMed Central is an extensive collection of open-access repository of peer-reviewed journal articles.
